    "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/posts/jan-meissner_i-do-many-calls-with-juniors-and-people-considering-activity-7090261521397612549-zNU2?utm_source=combined_share_message&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAAE0Wae8Bdw49TBBX9odwCVUCDyBMCOF71rc",
    "timeSincePosted": "2yr",
    "shareUrn": "urn:li:share:7090261518532980738",
    "text": "I do many calls with juniors and people considering a career switch into IT and tech, mainly thanks to Junior Guru & Honza Javorek. 🐣\n\nI wouldn't call it mentoring because it's usually not a long-term relationship. After all, I am more of a traffic light at the crossroad, helping to navigate whom to meet next and what should be the next steps.\n\nWhat do we usually talk about?\n\n💻 Getting to know each other. Thanks to such organizations as Junior Guru, everyone involved gets to meet people from different social circles and backgrounds. And it is truly eye-opening. Often those people are with some rough experiences, and it makes you appreciate their efforts even more.\n\n💻 I always try to find out whether their expectations of life in IT match the reality. And I like to be the reality check because (and it's no shame) it's not for everyone. And during such conversations, we can find out that a different role or path may be more suitable.\n\n💻 We look at the portfolio, Linkedin and previous efforts, and I try to point out everything I learned over the years in the business. 👨‍🦲\n\n💻 And the most essential thing, already mentioned above, I suggest either colleagues or people in other companies I know to get in further touch. \n\nWhy am I saying this? \n\nI want to encourage everyone to find a way to open themselves up to juniors and career switchers. Show them what it is to work in a tech company, what the office looks like, how you work and help them with your network. Contacts are the most valuable assets we have when used right. You can change someone's life, and there is something for you too. It is gratifying! And hey, we all want our companies to be here for a long time. Creating a new generation of engineers, analysts, and other skilled people is in everyone's interest. ✌",
